{{nihongo foot|'''''Syvalion'''''|サイバリオン|Saibarion|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} is an [[arcade game|arcade]] shooter [[video game]] released by [[Taito]] in 1988 and designed by [[Fukio Mitsuji]], creator of ''[[Bubble Bobble]]''. The player controls a golden metal dragon which flies around, breathing fire at its enemies while collecting power-ups to recharge its fire. The enemies are robots and tanks. At the end of each level, the player fights a boss.<ref name=Syvalion>{{cite web|title=Syvalion - Videogame by Taito|url=http://www.arcade-museum.com/game_detail.php?game_id=9991|publisher=The International Arcade Museum|accessdate=27 December 2012}}</ref>

It was re-released for the [[PlayStation 2]] as a part of ''[[Taito Legends 2]]'' in 2006.

==Trivia==
In ''[[Dariusburst]]'', also from Taito, the boss named Dark Helios changes form and appears to be the metal dragon from ''Syvalion''.

